body:
vtable addresses [may differ cross codegen units](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/46139). To mitigate this, it would be good to have a lint that warns against comparing wide pointers with vtables.

### Original report

This is a regression from the 2/27 to 2/28 nightly.

```rust
pub trait Trait {}
impl Trait for i32 {}

pub struct Obj<'a, T: 'static + Trait> {
    ptr: &'a T,
    trait_ptr: *const dyn Trait,
}

impl<'a, T: Trait + 'static> Drop for Obj<'a, T> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        assert_eq!(self.trait_ptr, self.ptr as *const dyn Trait);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let ptr = 5;
    let _name = Obj {
        ptr: &ptr,
        trait_ptr: &ptr,
    };
}
```

When this program is built with `rustc main.rs`, it runs without any trouble. When it's built with `rustc main.rs -C incremental=`, I receive the following output:
```
thread 'main' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)`
  left: `0x7ffee7d23864`,
 right: `0x7ffee7d23864`', main.rs:11:9
note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace
```

From the [regression window](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/compare/abc3073c9...6d69caba1), I suspect https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/67332.
